## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This TDD specifies the technical implementation of multi-format document indexing for the Kiro SDLC Agents VS Code extension.

### 1.2 Scope

* Modification of kiro-sdlc-agents/src/indexer.ts
* New module kiro-sdlc-agents/src/converter.ts
* Addition of filetomarkdown npm dependency
* Updated ingestion HTTP payload

### 1.3 Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Language | TypeScript | 5.4+ |
| Runtime | Node.js (VS Code bundled) | 18+ |
| Build Tool | esbuild | 0.21+ |
| Extension Host | VS Code Extension API | 1.85+ |
| Conversion | filetomarkdown | latest (pinned) |
| KB Backend | MCP Server (HTTP) | internal |

### 1.4 Design Principles

* Error Isolation: One file failure must not abort the batch
* Minimal Footprint: Avoid heavy native dependencies
* Progressive Enhancement: Extension works if filetomarkdown fails to load
* Idempotency: Re-running produces no duplicates
* Lazy Loading: filetomarkdown loaded only when needed

### 1.5 Constraints

* Must bundle with esbuild
* Must run within VS Code extension host memory
* Network calls limited to localhost
* Conversion timeout: 30 seconds per file

## 2. System Architecture

### 2.1 Architecture Overview

|  |
| --- |
| Architecture Diagram |

Architecture Diagram

Pipeline pattern: Command Handler to File Discovery to Format Router to Conversion to Ingestion.

Format Router splits into three paths: - Markdown: pass-through (read content directly) - Text (.txt, .csv, .json, .xml, .yaml): read as UTF-8, wrap in code block - Binary (.docx, .pdf, .xlsx, .png): convert via filetomarkdown

All paths converge at HTTP Ingest which sends to MCP Server KB.

### 2.2 Component Diagram

|  |
| --- |
| Component Diagram |

Component Diagram

| Component | Responsibility | Technology |
| --- | --- | --- |
| indexer.ts | Pipeline orchestration | TypeScript |
| converter.ts (NEW) | Conversion with timeout, size checks | TypeScript |
| discoverDocuments() | Recursive file scanning | Node.js fs |
| ingestDocumentsViaHttp() | HTTP POST to MCP server | Node.js http |
| filetomarkdown | Third-party conversion | npm package |

## 3. Module Design

### 3.1 File Structure

kiro-sdlc-agents/src/
|-- indexer.ts # MODIFIED
|-- converter.ts # NEW
|-- types/
 |-- indexer-types.ts # NEW

### 3.2 converter.ts Design

Key constants: - SIZE\_LIMITS: PDF 50MB, Images 20MB, default 50MB - TEXT\_FORMATS: txt, csv, json, xml, yaml, yml - CONVERSION\_TIMEOUT\_MS: 30000

Key function: convertFileToMarkdown(filePath, format) -> ConversionResult

Logic: 1. Check file exists, get size 2. Check size limit (skip if too large) 3. If text format: read as UTF-8, wrap in markdown code block 4. If binary: call filetomarkdown with 30s timeout 5. Return ConversionResult with success/error

Lazy loading: filetomarkdown loaded via require() on first use. If package unavailable, throw descriptive error.

### 3.3 indexer.ts Modifications

Changes: 1. Import convertFileToMarkdown from converter.ts 2. In document indexing path: separate md vs non-md files 3. Convert non-md files sequentially with progress updates 4. Update quick pick label to “Index all SDLC documents into Knowledge Base” 5. Enhanced ingest payload: add optional content field for pre-converted files

### 3.4 Type Definitions

interface ConversionResult {
 markdown: string;
 success: boolean;
 error: string | null;
 bytesProcessed: number;
 conversionTime: number;
}

interface DiscoveredDocument {
 path: string;
 type: string;
 ticket: string;
 format: string;
}

interface IndexStats {
 totalDiscovered: number;
 directMarkdown: number;
 converted: number;
 skipped: number;
 ingested: number;
 errors: Array<{ file: string; error: string }>;
}

## 4. Integration Design

### 4.1 filetomarkdown Package

| Attribute | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Package | filetomarkdown |
| Import | require (lazy loaded) |
| Bundling | Try inline first; externalize if native deps |
| Fallback | Skip binary conversions if unavailable |

package.json: "filetomarkdown": "^1.0.0"

### 4.2 MCP Server HTTP API

Enhanced payload supports optional content field: - If content present: server ingests content directly - If content absent: server reads file from file\_path (existing behavior)

Endpoint: POST http://localhost:{port}/api/memory/ingest-file

## 5. Error Handling

| Category | Handling | Notification |
| --- | --- | --- |
| File Access | Skip + continue | Output channel |
| Size Limit | Skip + continue | Output channel |
| Conversion Error | Skip + continue | Output channel |
| Timeout (>30s) | Abort + continue | Output channel |
| Network (MCP down) | Abort ingestion | Error toast |
| Package Unavailable | Disable binary conversion | Warning toast |

## 6. Security Design

* Path validation: Only files under workspace documents/
* No external network: All HTTP to localhost
* Size limits: Prevent memory exhaustion
* No secrets in logs

## 7. Performance

| Operation | Target | Strategy |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Single docx | < 3s | Lazy load, in-process |
| Single pdf | < 5s | 30s timeout cap |
| 50-file batch | < 2 min | Sequential processing |
| Memory | < 100MB increase | One file at a time |

